      "items": [
        {
          "type": "heading1",
          "verse_numbers": [],
          "lines": [
            "The Destruction of Nineveh"
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            1
          ],
          "lines": [
            "The scatterer has come up against you.",
            "Man the ramparts;",
            "watch the road;",
            "dress for battle;",
            "collect all your strength."
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            2
          ],
          "lines": [
            "For the Lord is restoring the majesty of Jacob",
            "as the majesty of Israel,",
            "for plunderers have plundered them",
            "and ruined their branches."
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            3
          ],
          "lines": [
            "The shield of his mighty men is red;",
            "his soldiers are clothed in scarlet.",
            "The chariots come with flashing metal",
            "on the day he musters them;",
            "the cypress spears are brandished."
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            4
          ],
          "lines": [
            "The chariots race madly through the streets;",
            "they rush to and fro through the squares;",
            "they gleam like torches;",
            "they dart like lightning."
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            5
          ],
          "lines": [
            "He remembers his officers;",
            "they stumble as they go,",
            "they hasten to the wall;",
            "the siege tower is set up."
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            6
          ],
          "lines": [
            "The river gates are opened;",
            "the palace melts away;"
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            7
          ],
          "lines": [
            "its mistress is stripped; she is carried off,",
            "her slave girls lamenting,",
            "moaning like doves",
            "and beating their breasts."
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            8
          ],
          "lines": [
            "Nineveh is like a pool",
            "whose waters run away.",
            "“Halt! Halt!” they cry,",
            "but none turns back."
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            9
          ],
          "lines": [
            "Plunder the silver,",
            "plunder the gold!",
            "There is no end of the treasure",
            "or of the wealth of all precious things."
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            10
          ],
          "lines": [
            "Desolate! Desolation and ruin!",
            "Hearts melt and knees tremble;",
            "anguish is in all loins;",
            "all faces grow pale!"
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            11
          ],
          "lines": [
            "Where is the lions’ den,",
            "the feeding place of the young lions,",
            "where the lion and lioness went,",
            "where his cubs were, with none to disturb?"
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            12
          ],
          "lines": [
            "The lion tore enough for his cubs",
            "and strangled prey for his lionesses;",
            "he filled his caves with prey",
            "and his dens with torn flesh."
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            13
          ],
          "lines": [
            "Behold, I am against you, declares the Lord of hosts, and I will burn your chariots in smoke, and the sword shall devour your young lions. I will cut off your prey from the earth, and the voice of your messengers shall no longer be heard."
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
