      "items": [
        {
          "type": "heading1",
          "verse_numbers": [],
          "lines": [
            "Woe to Nineveh"
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            1
          ],
          "lines": [
            "Woe to the bloody city,",
            "all full of lies and plunder—",
            "no end to the prey!"
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            2
          ],
          "lines": [
            "The crack of the whip, and rumble of the wheel,",
            "galloping horse and bounding chariot!"
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            3
          ],
          "lines": [
            "Horsemen charging,",
            "flashing sword and glittering spear,",
            "hosts of slain,",
            "heaps of corpses,",
            "dead bodies without end—",
            "they stumble over the bodies!"
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            4
          ],
          "lines": [
            "And all for the countless whorings of the prostitute,",
            "graceful and of deadly charms,",
            "who betrays nations with her whorings,",
            "and peoples with her charms."
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            5
          ],
          "lines": [
            "Behold, I am against you,",
            "declares the Lord of hosts,",
            "and will lift up your skirts over your face;",
            "and I will make nations look at your nakedness",
            "and kingdoms at your shame."
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            6
          ],
          "lines": [
            "I will throw filth at you",
            "and treat you with contempt",
            "and make you a spectacle."
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            7
          ],
          "lines": [
            "And all who look at you will shrink from you and say,",
            "“Wasted is Nineveh; who will grieve for her?”",
            "Where shall I seek comforters for you?"
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            8
          ],
          "lines": [
            "Are you better than Thebes",
            "that sat by the Nile,",
            "with water around her,",
            "her rampart a sea,",
            "and water her wall?"
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            9
          ],
          "lines": [
            "Cush was her strength;",
            "Egypt too, and that without limit;",
            "Put and the Libyans were her helpers."
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            10
          ],
          "lines": [
            "Yet she became an exile;",
            "she went into captivity;",
            "her infants were dashed in pieces",
            "at the head of every street;",
            "for her honored men lots were cast,",
            "and all her great men were bound in chains."
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            11
          ],
          "lines": [
            "You also will be drunken;",
            "you will go into hiding;",
            "you will seek a refuge from the enemy."
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            12
          ],
          "lines": [
            "All your fortresses are like fig trees",
            "with first-ripe figs—",
            "if shaken they fall",
            "into the mouth of the eater."
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            13
          ],
          "lines": [
            "Behold, your troops",
            "are women in your midst.",
            "The gates of your land",
            "are wide open to your enemies;",
            "fire has devoured your bars."
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            14
          ],
          "lines": [
            "Draw water for the siege;",
            "strengthen your forts;",
            "go into the clay;",
            "tread the mortar;",
            "take hold of the brick mold!"
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            15
          ],
          "lines": [
            "There will the fire devour you;",
            "the sword will cut you off.",
            "It will devour you like the locust.",
            "Multiply yourselves like the locust;",
            "multiply like the grasshopper!"
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            16
          ],
          "lines": [
            "You increased your merchants",
            "more than the stars of the heavens.",
            "The locust spreads its wings and flies away."
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            17
          ],
          "lines": [
            "Your princes are like grasshoppers,",
            "your scribes like clouds of locusts",
            "settling on the fences",
            "in a day of cold—",
            "when the sun rises, they fly away;",
            "no one knows where they are."
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            18
          ],
          "lines": [
            "Your shepherds are asleep,",
            "O king of Assyria;",
            "your nobles slumber.",
            "Your people are scattered on the mountains",
            "with none to gather them."
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "verse_numbers": [
            19
          ],
          "lines": [
            "There is no easing your hurt;",
            "your wound is grievous.",
            "All who hear the news about you",
            "clap their hands over you.",
            "For upon whom has not come",
            "your unceasing evil?"
          ],
          "rlw_lines": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}